main event: The witness observed a bright, colorful object in the sky that appeared to change shape and motion over the course of 31-60 minutes.
interesting points: The object appeared to change from star-like, to horizontal, to vertical, then back to horizontal before disappearing.
The object was brighter than the brightest stars.
The witness reported that the object appeared to stand still, suddenly speed up, break up into parts, give off smoke or exhaust, change shape, and disappear and reappear.
The witness could not determine the exact size, speed, or distance of the object.
The witness was 66 years old at the time of the sighting and reported it to the authorities.
sighted object: a bright, colorful object that changed shape and motion
